# DAP setVariable — `dap.set_variable` opens a prompt seeded with the
# selected variable's value. Without a live adapter there are no
# variables to set, so the command toasts the no-session / no-row
# state. Verifies the chord + prompt plumbing without a real adapter.

write code.rs "fn main() {}\n"
open code.rs

# With no debug session open, `dap.set_variable` is a no-op (no Pane::Debug
# means the early-return path fires). Just confirms the command exists.
command dap.set_variable
expect screen lacks "Set "

# Open the debug pane (no live session) — the variables panel will be
# empty so the chord still no-ops.
command dap.show
expect pane "Debug"

command dap.set_variable
expect screen lacks "Set "
